06/04/2004
TOKYO, Japan -- Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami met on Monday (5 April) with his counterpart from Serbia-Montenegro, Goran Svilanovic, on the sidelines of the Western Balkans conference in Tokyo. 
They discussed bilateral ties and the situation in Kosovo. 
Islami met also with Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi, discussing the need to continue dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina.
In other news Monday, Albania's Helsinki Committee voiced concern over the pace of implementing electoral reforms in the country. 
The committee says no concrete steps have been taken to meet the recommendations of an OSCE report. 
(ATA - 05/04/04)
